What does this TypeScript code tell you about the `users` variable?

```typescript
interface User {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  role: "admin" | "editor" | "viewer";
}

const users: User[] = [
  { id: 1, name: "Alice", role: "admin" },
  { id: 2, name: "Bob", role: "viewer" },
];
```

Look at this function signature. What does it expect, and what does it return?

```typescript
function formatPrice(amount: number, currency?: string): string {
  const symbol = currency === "EUR" ? "\u20ac" : "$";
  return `${symbol}${amount.toFixed(2)}`;
}
```

A developer asks you to review this TypeScript interface for a dashboard component. What can you tell them about the data shape?

```typescript
interface DashboardData {
  title: string;
  metrics: {
    revenue: number;
    users: number;
    conversionRate: number;
  };
  lastUpdated: string;
  alerts?: string[];
  comparisonPeriod?: "week" | "month" | "quarter";
}
```
